runs.comm: fullish delivery knocked back to the bowler
shout for leg before as he sweeps a full ball, but there is an inside edge too
deftly done, flat length ball outside off, he wristily runs it to the third man boundary
jumps out now to drive it straight down the ground, long on is around
comes in with the angle and is pushed on the up through extra cover
shortish ball, punched back, bowler fails to stop it as he slides clumsily
back of a length ball punched on the up, cover dives to stop it
overpitched into the pad, flicked in the air, well clear of short fine leg
wants to dismiss this length ball on the up, but is beaten as he flays from the crease
length ball tucking him up on middle and leg, nudged to midwicket
slants into the pad again, he cannot work it away
four more, another one into the pad, flicked uppishly, falls in front of the diving short fine leg and rushes past
gets too close to the pitch as he comes out and drives to mid off
quickish length ball turned to long on
slanted in fullish, pushed firmly to extra cover
tries to force this tossed up ball away, it goes to midwicket
flat and quick, staying low close to off, cut to backward point for a tight single
width provided on a shortish ball, and he rocks back to put it away through cover
first one down, Myburgh stands on the crease and tries to launch this length ball out of sight, merely sends it soaring high, and Tauqir makes no mistake at cover
good length ball, thumped on the up, past cover, lovely timing
charges out and heaves, gets a thick edge down to third man
firmly pushed straight to mid off
goes over midwicket, on the front foot, hasn't timed it too well, but clears the circle comfortably
moves across and taps a length ball to mid on
comes out and tries to go with the spin on the leg side, but is hit on the pad
tossed up ball pushed to covers
down the track to hit it to wide long on
eases a full one past the bowler, but mid on prevents the single
full delivery knocked back to the bowler
short and darted in, punched to midwicket, end of a tight over
stays on the crease and checks his shot to push a length ball down the track
Barresi's made some room, stepped out and drilled this full delivery straight to mid off, all those dots last over working for UAE
shortish, hitting the defensive bat hard and rolling on to the off side
full into the pad, worked to wide mid on
wide length ball, he stretches to reach it and crashes it past backward point
nice carry to the keeper from just back of a length, left alone
spins in a bit to middle, nudged to midwicket
works it squarer for a single now
punches a flat and shortish one to long on
paddles it from around off to long leg
overpitched, forced to long on for one more
full, eased down to wide long off
short of a good length, tapped in front of point
driven through extra cover, they push for the second as long off runs around, non-striker makes it as the throw comes in
length ball knocked down to long on
cramped for room with a short of a length ball slanted in
138 kph full delivery, he is surprised by the pace, and checks his push down the ground
short of a length ball, just outside off, pushed down the track
tries a big slog sweep, but misses a straighter one outside off
moves forward and turns it to midwicket
cannot get it past midwicket again
jumps out, bowler shortens the length, and midwicket is in business again
and yet again, stands on the crease and works it to midwicket
forcing shot this time, but there is no getting this full delivery past the man at midwicket
scoops a drive over extra cover off this full and wide one, enough time to take two
low full toss driven off the inner part of the bat to midwicket
into the pad, worked to deep square leg
walks across and outside the crease but is tucked up again with a short of a length ball
he is really struggling out there, Swart, forces a length ball straight to midwicket, and takes on the throw, which misses
appeal for leg before, but that pitched outside leg
length ball close to off, pushed to the bowler
tentatively looks to push this fullish delivery, is hit on the pad
that is bowled miles outside off, keeper does well to reach it
plays from back in the crease, knocks it to midwicket
manages to get off strike with a single to long on, this is a proper struggle at the moment for Netherlands
Swart releases some of the pressure with a swept boundary behind square
takes on midwicket once more with a nudge, scrambles across, throw misses again
low full toss on the pad, he walks out and works it to deep midwicket
that will help Netherlands feel a lot more comfortable, Cooper on his knee and lifts this length ball very cleanly over dee backward square
drives an overpitched ball to wide long off
slower length ball on the pad, worked in front of square
short of a length, turned to deep square leg
nudged with the angle in to the pad, that was travelling before short fine dived to stop it
tossed up from the left-armer, driven to long on
shout for leg before as he misses a sweep, that could have struck him just outside the line, and was not turning enough in any case
flays a length ball straight to cover
tossed up low full toss driven to long off
wide near yorker, he runs it off a thick edge to short third man
sits up on off, he rocks back and thumps it in front of square, sweeper is up to it with a dash to his left
sweeps a full ball on off hard but straight to deep square
skips out but fails to get it past midwicket, non striker was rushing for the single, and returned just in time, a better throw could have had him
hit through covers for a single
forces a flat delivery to long off
full ball worked to deep midwicket
Tauqir goes for maximum last ball of a tight spell, as Cooper gets down on his knee and connects well on the slog-sweep, sends it over deep midwicket
flighted really full outside off, guided to point
Swart's struggle has ended finally, went down to try a slog-sweep, missed the pitched up delivery, which crashed into middle
paddles a full delivery off his pads fine down the leg side
slanted in full, nudged through midwicket
punches a length ball straight to the bowler
that will help, widish ball, he was already making some room and makes sure he punches it well wide of the sweeper
down the track, this is slanted into his pads, he awkwardly nudges it square
attacks a full one, off a thick inside edge to deep midwicket
tries the reverse sweep early, and hits it in the air, just out of the reach of backward point
another reverse sweep, does not get hold of it this time
goes back in the crease to work it to long on
another thick inside edge to deep square as he goes after a full one
tossed up length ball, he stays on the crease and punches it to wide long off, where there is a misfield
good straight hit, was tossed up, and full enough for him to get under it outside off and clobber it over the bowler
forces it to long off for one to go to his fifty, he's guided this chase
Borren now, takes this from outside off and slams a slog sweep to deep midwicket
four more, this is overpitched on the pad, and he's dragged a sweep past short fine leg
takes a flighted ball from outside off and works it through midwicket, will be getting only the single
Borren skips out, and lifts the length ball all the way over the deep midwicket boundary, sealing the win in style
